In a exciting experience The Proteas and Spingboks, are set to face each other in the Nelson Mandela Legacy Cup in Cape Town on Thursday, 8 December .The two teams first meet in match of this kind took place at PPC Newlands on 3 January 2014 , when the Proteas dug deep to beat the Boks by 14 runs.The new faces in the Bok team include Rohan Janse van Rensburg, Sergeal Petersen, Trevor Nyakane, experienced Blitzbok Stephan Dippenaar, as well as former Bok fullbacks Conrad Jantjes and Percy Montgomery, all of whom will make their Bok cricketing debuts.Get your tickets for Proteas vs Springboks on 8 December in Cape Town here: https://t.co/s0PdD22EVs #MandelaCup16 pic.twitter.com/MiAp1Wm2u0 Cricket South Africa (@OfficialCSA) December 1, 2016Cricket SA s Head of Commercial and Marketing, Clive Eksteen told the CSA website at the announcement of the venue earlier this month ,that the day promises to be lots of fun but also serve as a memory to the legacy left behind by our late president, Nelson Mandela, as we celebrate the contribution he has made to our beautiful country.The Proteas have concentrated on T20 specialists such as David Miller, Imran Tahir and Aaron Phangiso with the only uncapped player being wicket-keeper Mangaliso Mosehle who was the Player of the Match in last season s franchise T20 Final.In its third edition match aims to raise substantial funds for the Nelson Mandela Foundation.Fans are encouraged to make their donations to the Nelson Mandela Foundation via a dedicated SMS line on match day.Proteas squad:Hashim Amla (BuildNat Cape Cobras), Mangaliso Mosehle (bizhub Highveld Lions), Faf du Plessis (Multiply Titans), JP Duminy (BuildNat Cape Cobras), David Miller (VKB Knights), Farhaan Behardien (Multiply Titans), Wayne Parnell (BuildNat Cape Cobras), Dwaine Pretorius (bizhub Highveld Lions), Aaron Phangiso (bizhub Highveld Lions), Imran Tahir (Hollywoodbets Dolphins), Kyle Abbott (Warriors)The Springbok squad includes:Damian de Allende, Faf de Klerk, Jean de Villiers, Stephan Dippenaar, Butch James, Rohan Janse van Rensburg, Conrad Jantjes, Pat Lambie (captain), Tiaan Liebenberg, Percy Montgomery, Trevor Nyakane, Sergeal PetersenNon-playing reserve: Siya Kolisi&nbsp;